field biologist and lab technician the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources login fellowships positions early career environmental scholars new fellowships new positions field biologist and lab technician field biologist and lab technician institution prince william sound science center discipline marine science type of position assistant scientist notes the biologist lab technician will assist both in the lab and on research cruises collecting samples and data related to a herring research project the majority of work involves preparation and analysis of fish laboratory samples sample management and data entry the technician will be expected to perform laboratory analytical protocols including otolith and scale removal and bomb calorimetry some of the lab samples are prepared for stable isotope analysis at labs outside of cordova the technician will complete additional lab and field duties as prescribed by dr thomas kline for more information see the position announcement submitted by leopold program staff march 6 2012 deadline march 19 2012 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
